1
00:00:23,041 --> 00:00:24,166
[KATSUSHIRO]
I'll get you out!

2
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:25,250
Go!

3
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:27,416
There has to be some other way!

4
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,041
Heihachi-dono...

5
00:00:36,125 --> 00:00:39,291
[HEIHACHI]
I'll be in the rice!

6
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:54,833
Kyuzo-dono!

7
00:00:54,916 --> 00:00:56,916
[KATSUSHIRO gasps]

8
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,958
[KAMBEI] I need you to
keep living Katsushiro...

9
00:01:06,041 --> 00:01:08,250
...until this job's done.

10
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:16,833
♪ opening song ♪

11
00:02:48,958 --> 00:02:50,583
It's Heihachi's...

12
00:02:57,208 --> 00:03:02,166
[rumbling]

13
00:03:04,625 --> 00:03:06,500
[BANDIT DRONE LEADER] Emperor,
communications are down.

14
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:08,375
Awaiting your command.

15
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:12,125
I'm starting to think this
thing isn't going to stop.

16
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,125
[PRIME MINISTER]
Its inertia will

17
00:03:13,208 --> 00:03:14,625
push it across the
ravine, Emperor.

18
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,625
The village will be destroyed.

19
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:20,250
[UKYO] Well, that was the goal,
so I suppose we win either way.

20
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,791
Now then...
Which way is the exit?

21
00:03:22,875 --> 00:03:24,125
[PRIME MINISTER]
I'll show you.

22
00:03:24,208 --> 00:03:26,125
There's a luxury vessel
prepared for your escape.

23
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:27,750
[UKYO]
How thoughtful.

24
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,458
Now be sure to use all
the Main Cannon's ammunition

25
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:31,291
before you leave.

26
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:32,583
[PRIME MINISTER]
Of course.

27
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:39,833
Oh dear, they won't
be easy to replace.

28
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:42,916
[MANZO] Nothing's working!
The Capital won't stop!

29
00:03:44,166 --> 00:03:45,875
There's got to be some
way to slow it down!

30
00:03:45,958 --> 00:03:48,625
It's going to wipe out
our entire village!

31
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:54,291
[PRIME MINISTER] No,
not the escape ship!

32
00:03:54,375 --> 00:03:56,500
[UKYO] What in
the world is this?

33
00:03:56,583 --> 00:03:58,208
I'm terribly sorry, Emperor.

34
00:03:58,291 --> 00:04:00,625
How could you let this
happen?! Where are they?!

35
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:02,000
I--

36
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:04,041
[crashing sounds]

37
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:13,750
[whimpering]

38
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:16,083
[KIKUCHIYO] Guess
Kambei was right.

39
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:18,750
The real one would
try to escape.

40
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,500
No! Not you!

41
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,791
[SHICHIROJI] I dunno...
Maybe he's a fake, too.

42
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:32,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Don't worry.
I got the perfect test.

43
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:34,125
[KATSUSHIRO]
What are you going to do?

44
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:40,625
[KIKUCHIYO] 
Oh yeah. Smells pretty girly.

45
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:42,750
If he smells like court ladies,
he must be real--

46
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,875
they wouldn't waste
perfume on a fake.

47
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:46,083
No, I'm just a farmer!

48
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,750
They gave me a bath
when I got here!

49
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,625
[KIKUCHIYO] 
Enough! Your acting's terrible.

50
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,291
But you were a farmer
once, weren't you?

51
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:56,416
I was too. So I know why
you'd want to rule the world.

52
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,291
Hell, I turned myself into
metal to climb the ladder.

53
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:02,250
But you must've learned some
dignity from the upper class.

54
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,083
So have a little self-respect

55
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:07,375
and slit your
stomach like a man.

56
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:09,541
If you really were a farmer
once, then you should know

57
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:11,916
how important it is
that I remain Emperor.

58
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,166
Peasants like us spent our lives
tormented by the Nobuseri.

59
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:17,666
Now that I'm in control,
I can change that for good--

60
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,083
that's the point of all this!

61
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:21,333
I'm doing what I must
to set the peasants free,

62
00:05:21,416 --> 00:05:23,500
and yet here you are
trying to murder me!

63
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:26,333
Stop feeding me lies,
you bastard!

64
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:27,916
[UKYO] Don't shoot!

65
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:32,291
If you kill me, then life will
only return to the way it was.

66
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:34,666
Kanna has to be sacrificed
to keep the peace--

67
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,416
a small price to pay to
live in a world of order.

68
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,291
Kambei taught me
a long time ago,

69
00:05:39,375 --> 00:05:41,666
when samurai raise
their swords...

70
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:44,375
...they don't hesitate
to bring 'em down!

71
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:45,875
[screaming]

72
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:47,666
[booming sound]

73
00:05:54,708 --> 00:05:56,541
Kikuchiyo- <i>dono</i> !

74
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:06,125
[KIKUCHIYO] Damn cowards.

75
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,083
I hate machine samurai!

76
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:12,083
I hate them, I hate
them, I hate them!

77
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:13,750
Treating me like
a filthy insect!

78
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,416
--Get off him!
--And the old Emperor,

79
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,750
I hate him, too!

80
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:19,375
Making me a peasant to be
bullied by you machines,

81
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:22,416
all for his stupid plan
I never asked to be a part of!

82
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:25,250
Merchants! Peasants!
Samurai! Machines!

83
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,750
I hate you all!

84
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,791
I'll turn this whole
world upside down!

85
00:06:28,875 --> 00:06:31,416
I'll treat you all like bugs!

86
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,250
Anyway, we should be going.

87
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,000
Emperor.

88
00:06:43,083 --> 00:06:44,625
[GUARD LEADER] But the
escape ship is disabled.

89
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:46,375
Well, then get one of
those Bandits out there

90
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:47,916
to carry it with us in it!

91
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,333
You're not too bright, are you?

92
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,666
[GUARD LEADER] No,
Emperor. Forgive me.

93
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:58,541
[explosion sounds]

94
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,708
Tell me where Kambei is.

95
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,375
I don't know.

96
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:14,166
Huh... Is that so?

97
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:17,791
[screaming]

98
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:19,541
Stop!

99
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:21,500
I won't ask again.

100
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:26,791
[GUARD LEADER] Your Excellency,
please board the escape ship.

101
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:29,333
[UKYO] By the way,
how is my Kirara?

102
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:30,958
Considering the Capital
here is going to

103
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:32,500
wipe out her entire village,

104
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:36,458
I need to know where
she is so I can rescue her.

105
00:07:36,541 --> 00:07:38,458
[GUARD LEADER] Your...
Your Excellency...

106
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,666
What? I'm in the
middle of something!

107
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,583
[screaming]

108
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:03,041
[BANDIT DRONE 2] Samurai.

109
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:07,041
Raise a sword to the
Emperor and we attack.

110
00:08:07,125 --> 00:08:09,041
[UKYO] Wait, you idiots!
Don't fire in here!

111
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,208
You'll kill us all!

112
00:08:10,291 --> 00:08:11,583
[BANDIT DRONE 2]
We must protect you.

113
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:14,583
Sensei...
The Bandits are mine.

114
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:18,791
W-Wait! It was the
former Emperor who

115
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:21,583
made deals with the Nobuseri,
stealing rice and women!

116
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:23,500
I wasn't even here!

117
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:27,041
But you are the
Emperor now, Ukyo.

118
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:28,500
No, it was him--
the Prime Minister,

119
00:08:28,583 --> 00:08:30,000
he was the one in control!

120
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:32,375
He came to me in Kougakyo,
said he needed someone killed

121
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,458
and if I helped him, he'd
let me make the world better!

122
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:35,875
But he tricked me!

123
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:38,000
I just wanted to give
everyone's lives more pleasure,

124
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:39,916
but he said sacrifices
had to be made!

125
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,833
He said we had to destroy
Kanna! I didn't want to!

126
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:45,166
You can't kill an Emperor!

127
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:47,083
You'll be a traitor
to your people!

128
00:08:47,166 --> 00:08:49,291
So be it.

129
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:51,083
[screaming]

130
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:59,208
[BANDIT DRONE 2] Cursed samurai!

131
00:09:02,958 --> 00:09:06,333
[explosion]

132
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:20,500
Katsushiro, take care of
the rest of the Nobuseri.

133
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,041
Right!

134
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:23,750
[SHICHIROJI] Kambei- <i>sama</i> ,
you're hurt pretty bad.

135
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,208
[KAMBEI] Don't worry about me.

136
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:28,208
We have to stop the Capital
from crossing the ravine.

137
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:29,750
[SHICHIROJI] You got it.

138
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:37,708
Kikuchiyo!

139
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,583
[BANDIT DRONE 3]
I have you, Emperor.

140
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,458
[RIKICHI] Kikuchiyo!

141
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:02,541
Kiku, can you hear me in there?

142
00:10:02,625 --> 00:10:04,416
Are you going to be okay?

143
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:07,416
[KIKUCHIYO] Yeah...

144
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:17,291
Kirara! There you are!

145
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:18,333
[gasping]

146
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,291
[UKYO laughing]

147
00:10:28,208 --> 00:10:30,416
[BANDIT DRONE 3] Emperor.
You require medical attention!

148
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,208
My lovely jewel.

149
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:35,166
What's wrong with him?!
He's scaring me!

150
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:39,458
I knew it...
You came to rescue me!

151
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:49,416
Things were so confusing before
you appeared... Thank you.

152
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,000
[BANDIT DRONE 3]
Emperor, please.

153
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:54,833
Everyone else is dead, but you
and I can return to Paradise!

154
00:10:56,375 --> 00:11:00,333
Get away from them, you creep!

155
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:02,750
[BANDIT DRONE 3] Traitor!

156
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:07,333
[metal clanging]

157
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:14,125
[metal chinking]

158
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:16,125
[explosion]

159
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,708
[KIRARA] Kikuchiyo!

160
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:22,791
[KOMACHI] Kiku, you're hurt.

161
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:26,166
[KIKUCHIYO] There's
no time for pain now.

162
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:30,250
Rikichi, take me right
in front of the Capital.

163
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:33,500
[booms]

164
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:56,083
Now get outta' here.

165
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:58,208
You can do it, Kiku! I know it!

166
00:11:58,291 --> 00:11:59,625
[KIKUCHIYO] You're
the greatest, sprout!

167
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:01,041
Please be careful!

168
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:02,833
[KIKUCHIYO] Y'can count on me.

169
00:12:40,875 --> 00:12:45,833
[metal clinking]

170
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:59,833
You're not making it to Kanna,
you Capital piece of crap!

171
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:08,625
You got a full-fledged
samurai making sure of it!

172
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:41,666
[crashing sounds]

173
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:43,416
Let's get out of here.

174
00:14:16,791 --> 00:14:19,500
Kirara, my jewel...

175
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:30,916
[explosion]

176
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:45,583
[whimpering]

177
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:48,708
[ELDER] Lay down your weapons.

178
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:51,541
This war is finally over.

179
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:40,625
Come out, Nobuseri!
Where are you?!

180
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:44,166
I'll kill you!
I'll kill you all!

181
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:46,666
The Nobuseri are dead,
Katsushiro...

182
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,208
And the Capital is no more.

183
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:56,208
It appears we have
survived yet again.

184
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:58,500
Yeah, I guess we have.

185
00:16:02,125 --> 00:16:06,750
[sniveling]

186
00:17:10,416 --> 00:17:12,000
Grandmother...

187
00:17:12,083 --> 00:17:13,541
Are you certain of this?

188
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:17,875
Passing the Dowsing
Crystal to Komachi?

189
00:17:17,958 --> 00:17:21,125
You've seen it, too... My
days as Priestess are over.

190
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:23,291
[SETSU] You mean the
tainting of the water?

191
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:25,833
Yes, I've seen it.

192
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:29,125
It symbolizes my impurity--
my sins from this war.

193
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:31,375
My dear girl,
it's not your fault.

194
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:33,083
Stop blaming yourself and think.

195
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:36,333
Do you really want
to make this decision?

196
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:04,458
[footsteps]

197
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,833
I swore I'd protect you.

198
00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:11,916
But for a long time,
I was the one being protected.

199
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,041
You told me we'd fall together

200
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:17,541
and you will never know how
much strength that gave me.

201
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:19,958
--[KIRARA] Katsushiro, I--
--The scent of battle...

202
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,583
To please you,
I yearned for it,

203
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:24,583
but to get it, I had
to deny my heart.

204
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:38,958
Are we interrupting?

205
00:19:43,666 --> 00:19:45,125
[KATSUSHIRO] All
this time, Sensei,

206
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:47,166
I've wondered what
it was you saw in me,

207
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:50,291
what made you choose me
as the fifth samurai...

208
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:52,416
And with every battle,
every wound...

209
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,083
...I got a little
closer to the truth.

210
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,958
You told me once
not to value death.

211
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:02,791
You told me to live on and to
finish what I'd begun...

212
00:20:02,875 --> 00:20:04,416
And yet,

213
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:07,250
these brave men who had
nothing to gain from this war

214
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:10,375
who did give their lives
in the defense of Kanna...

215
00:20:10,458 --> 00:20:13,583
Aren't they the most
noble samurai of us all?

216
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:16,208
Do you feel ashamed
for surviving?

217
00:20:17,291 --> 00:20:20,416
No... It means I can
fight new battles...

218
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,833
Find more chances
to honor their names...

219
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:26,125
...just as you have, Sensei.

220
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,750
I pass this to you.

221
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:44,416
I'll use it well.

222
00:21:19,916 --> 00:21:24,833
♪ Today a cherry
blossom blooms ♪

223
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:31,083
♪ The dark rain tries to stop ♪

224
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:38,333
♪ What should I,
a poor peasant, do? ♪

225
00:21:38,416 --> 00:21:44,333
♪ Nurture the young rice crop ♪

226
00:21:45,541 --> 00:21:48,750
♪ Once the fields are
tiered and trimmed ♪

227
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:52,833
♪ Then bring the water,
winter's ice ♪

228
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:56,458
♪ Fill the paddies
to the brim ♪

229
00:21:56,541 --> 00:21:59,291
♪ It's time to plant the rice ♪

230
00:21:59,375 --> 00:22:01,375
[RIKICHI winces]

231
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,416
Sanae, you're up...

232
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,666
Let me take over for a while...

233
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:12,166
After all, we are
a team, aren't we?

234
00:22:12,250 --> 00:22:13,833
[RIKICHI laughs]

235
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:20,208
♪ Let clumps of
weeds wither away ♪

236
00:22:20,291 --> 00:22:26,125
♪ I do not want them here ♪

237
00:22:26,208 --> 00:22:29,250
Once again, old friend,
we fought a losing battle.

238
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:31,000
Huh?

239
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:34,416
This war's victory goes to the
farmers, the rice, and the soil.

240
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:37,291
But not to you and me.

241
00:22:37,375 --> 00:22:43,083
[FARMERS continue singing]

242
00:22:43,166 --> 00:22:47,625
Empires rise and fall,
but the land is forever.

243
00:22:52,583 --> 00:22:55,208
We take our leave, Elder.

244
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:57,458
Now is a farmer's season.

245
00:23:09,541 --> 00:23:12,708
♪ Weeds are picked
and water splashed ♪

246
00:23:12,791 --> 00:23:16,958
♪ Don't slow until it's done ♪

247
00:23:17,041 --> 00:23:25,541
♪ Put in constant effort and
sweet tasting rice will come ♪

248
00:23:43,291 --> 00:23:48,250
♪ closing song ♪

249
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:24,291
[KOMACHI]
Well, this is it.

250
00:25:24,375 --> 00:25:25,541
The war's over.

251
00:25:25,625 --> 00:25:27,958
But Kiku isn't here
to share it with me.

252
00:25:28,041 --> 00:25:29,666
The fight that started
with the Bandits

253
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:32,666
and went on with Ukyo becoming
Emperor was hard on us all,

254
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:34,916
especially the brave
samurai who died

255
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,458
so we could live in peace.

256
00:25:36,541 --> 00:25:38,416
I promise never to forget them.

257
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:41,125
But I'm not just gonna remember
the sad and painful things.

258
00:25:41,208 --> 00:25:43,000
I'll remember all
the happy stuff, too.

259
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:46,625
Like Heihachi's easygoing ways
and Gorobei's funny tricks.

260
00:25:46,708 --> 00:25:49,625
I'll remember every samurai,
because we needed them all.

261
00:25:49,708 --> 00:25:51,125
It's like Heihachi said.

262
00:25:51,208 --> 00:25:54,000
There are seven kami who
live in the rice and protect it,

263
00:25:54,083 --> 00:25:55,833
and that's what these
seven were for us.

264
00:25:55,916 --> 00:25:58,375
So thank you,
serious-talking Kambei,

265
00:25:58,458 --> 00:26:00,041
and smooth-talking Shichiroji,

266
00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:02,583
and Kyuzo, who hardly
talked at all.

267
00:26:02,666 --> 00:26:05,583
And thank you, Kiku,
for being my best friend,

268
00:26:05,666 --> 00:26:08,166
and the most bravest
samurai there is.

269
00:26:08,250 --> 00:26:10,333
I'll keep your scroll forever...

270
00:26:10,416 --> 00:26:12,750
Well, it's late and
I better get my sleep.

271
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,625
After all, I'm the
Water Priestess now

272
00:26:14,708 --> 00:26:16,250
and I'm gonna be busy!

273
00:26:16,333 --> 00:26:18,375
Okay. Bye-bye!

